            Fund Description
        




The fund seeks capital appreciation by investing at least 80% of its net assets in the securities of companies around the world that mine, process or deal in gold and other precious metals such as platinum, palladium and silver. The fund has a secondary goal of current income.



            Strategy Statement
        








"We think precious metals are attractive because they are a hard asset that's not tied to a particular country or financial system, potentially providing stability in times of economic uncertainty.
"                                            
                                            












Management







Steve Land, CFA®

Joined Franklin Templeton in 1997
Managed Fund Since 1999










Fred Fromm, CFA®

Joined Franklin Templeton in 1992
Managed Fund Since 1993











